255,'_elementor_template_type','post'),(1241,255,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1242,255,'_elementor_data','[{\"id\":\"8934367\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"1711149\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5bb2ad8\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>We built a system that sees the position of a toy car using a camera fixed to the ceiling and drives it automatically to the desired location.<\\/p><p>We coded the system in MATLAB. We used image processing to identify the car\'s position and destination and we coded 3 different methods of control to guide the car to the destination.<\\/p><p>The image processing technique we used was background subtraction. This method easily detects the car since it\'s the only object moving in the environment. A Gaussian filter was applied to reduce the noise after subtraction and then a threshold was applied and the remaining pixel locations was averaged to get the car\'s location. The process is shown below.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"},{\"id\":\"1fe0c25\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"carousel\":[{\"id\":249,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/03\\/Car.png\"},{\"id\":250,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/03\\/car2.png\"},{\"id\":251,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/03\\/car3.png\"},{\"id\":252,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/03\\/car4.png\"}],\"thumbnail_size\":\"large\",\"link_to\":\"file\",\"caption_type\":\"caption\",\"infinite\":\"no\",\"arrows_position\":\"outside\",\"arrows_color\":\"#000000\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image-carousel\"},{\"id\":\"338ec03\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>We used a cheap remote controlled toy car we bought from the local market and we modified its motor because it was too fast to be control