alse}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"dca5edf\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"60fa5fe\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"0ae1cb6\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"spacer\"},{\"id\":\"d8d78a4\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"<p id=\\\"Projects\\\">Projects<\\/p>\",\"title_color\":\"rgba(0,0,0,0.99)\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Arial\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"53c7b03\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"tabs\":[{\"tab_title\":\"Chores Tracker using PIC16f88 MCU\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>Nov 2019<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/Chores-Tracker-using-pic16f88-mcu\\/\\\">Click here<\\/a><\\/p><p>I created\\u00a0 a system to keep track of chores in the house using a PIC16f88 micro controller. I programmed the micro controller in C.<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"b2a2830\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>Dec 2018<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/implementation-of-cyclic-redundancy-check-on-fpga\\/\\\">Click here<\\/a><\\/p><p>I implemented three Cyclic Redundancy Check algorithms (CRC-8 , CRC-5 , CRC-3) on Intle\'s FPGA board DE2-70 using VHDL.<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"f088114\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Implementation of Tree Pattern Matching\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>May 2018<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/implementation-of-tree-pattern-matching\\/\\\">Click Here<\\/a><\\/p><p>We implemented an algorithm for tree pattern matching described in the IEEE paper \\\"A Parallel Algorithm and Architecture for Object Recognition in Images\\\".<\\/p><p>We used VHDL to implement the algorithm, and we added our own designed components to control data flow through the circuit.<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"0de8aeb\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Design of a Wearable Augmented Reality System\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>May 2017<\\/p><p>Designed a simple augmented reality system using available components in the market.<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"8e835f4\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Visually Servoed RC Toy Car\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>Dec 2015<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/visually-servoed-rc-toy-car\\/\\\">Click Here<\\/a><\\/p><p>It was my capstone project for my undergraduate degree.\\u00a0We built a system that senses the position of a toy car and drives it automatically to the desired location through a PC.<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"e0e4521\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Power System Design and Analysis\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>May 2015<\\/p><p><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Learned how to use ETAP software and designed a simple power network and analyzed it.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"39efa38\"}]},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"accordion\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"2e1a31a\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2b726ec\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2114164\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"spacer\"},{\"id\":\"51284d3\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"<p id=\\\"Skills\\\">Skills<\\/p>\",\"title_color\":\"rgba(0,0,0,0.99)\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Arial\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"6a52681\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2ded8ee\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"3327f42\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<ul><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Microsoft Office Suite<\\/span><\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">C<\\/span><\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Python<\\/span><\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Matlab<\\/span><\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Assembly<\\/span><\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">VHDL<\\/span><\\/li><\\/ul>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":true},{\"id\":\"a14fa1c\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"4c82420\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<ul><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Mentor Graphics<\\/span><\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">HSPICE<\\/span><\\/li><li>PLC Programming<\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Arduino<\\/span><\\/li><li>Fusion 360<\\/li><li><span class=\\\"fontstyle0\\\">Languages: English, Arabic, Spanish (elementary)<\\/span><\\/li><\\/ul>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":true}],\"isInner\":true}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),(1594,322,'_elementor_version','0.4'),(1595,322,'_elementor_edit_mode','builder'),(1596,322,'_elementor_css','a:4:{s:4:\"time\";i:1577753419;s:5:\"fonts\";a:1:{i:0;s:5:\"Arial\";}s:6:\"status\";s:4:\"file\";i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(1598,323,'_edit_lock','1577757338:1'),(1599,323,'_elementor_edit_mode','builder'),(1600,323,'_elementor_template_type','post'),(1601,323,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1602,323,'_elementor_data','[{\"id\":\"ad94a4d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ca5d9ce\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b48047a\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>I wanted to connect the AC thermostat in the house we are living in right now to the internet so we can control it through our phones instead of having to do it manually. So I designed and built a system to do that.<\\/p><p>I designed a mechanical module with a servo motor that can be taped on the thermostat to control it, and I connected the servo motor to the ESP01 micro controller. ESP01 is an IOT micro controller that can be programmed using different methods, I programmed it using the Arduion IDE.<\\/p><p>I used an APP called Blynk to to connect to the phone because it\'s free and it provides a very good GUI.<\\/p><p>Since we are not the owners of the house, I didn\'t want to change anything in the wiring of the thermostat or do any permanent changes.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"},{\"id\":\"64a2157\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"carousel\":[{\"id\":330,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/12\\/IMG_20191230_120557.jpg\"},{\"id\":331,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/12\\/IMG_20191230_120622-e1577755468609.jpg\"},{\"id\":332,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/12\\/IMG_20191230_120713-e1577755480682.jpg\"}],\"thumbnail_size\":\"boxstyle-list\",\"link_to\":\"file\",\"image_spacing\":\"custom\",\"image_border_border\":\"solid\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image-carousel\"},{\"id\":\"ae32923\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>I got the pinion gear and pusher design from a listing on\\u00a0<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.thingiverse.com\\/thing:3170748\\\">thingiverse<\\/a>\\u00a0and I modified them to fit what I need. I also designed the enclosure for the electronics.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"},{\"id\":\"b50fd65\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"carousel\":[{\"id\":343,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/12\\/Capture2.png\"},{\"id\":341,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/waseemorphali.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/12\\/Capture.png\"}],\"thumbnail_size\":\"boxstyle-list\",\"link_to\":\"file\",\"image_spacing\":\"custom\",\"image_border_border\":\"solid\",\"_margin\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"132\",\"isLinked\":false},\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image-carousel\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),(1603,325,'_elementor_edit_mode','builder'),(1604,325,'_elementor_template_type','post'),(1605,325,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1606,325,'_elementor_data','[{\"id\":\"ad94a4d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ca5d9ce\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b48047a\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>I wanted to connect the AC thermostat in the house we are living in right now to the internet so we can control it through our phones instead of having to do it manually. So I designed and built a system to do that.<\\/p><p>I designed a mechanical module with a servo motor that can be taped on the thermostat to control it, and I connected the servo motor to the ESP01 micro controller. ESP01 is an IOT micro controller that can be programmed using different methods, I programmed it using the Arduion IDE.<\\/p><p>I used an APP called Blynk to to connect to the phone because it\'s free and it provides a very good GUI.<\\/p><p>Since we are not the owners of the house, I didn\'t want to change anything in the wiring of the thermostat or do any permanent changes.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),(1607,323,'_elementor_version','0.4'),(1637,333,'_elementor_edit_mode','builder'),(1638,333,'_elementor_template_type','post'),(1639,333,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1640,333,'_elementor_data','[{\"id\":\"ad94a4d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ca5d9ce\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b48047a\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>I wanted to connect the AC thermostat in the house we are living in right now to the internet so we can control it through our phones instead of having to do it manually. So I designed and built a system to do that.<\\/p><p>I designed a mechanical module with a servo motor that can be taped on the thermostat to control it, and I connected the servo motor to t