ta-elementor-lightbox-index=\"0\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150730_095112-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150730_095112\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150614_141040-e1552265732695.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"1\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150614_141040-e1552265149822-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150614_141040\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150615_150921-e1552265753299.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"2\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150615_150921-e1552265672456-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150615_150921\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150730_095504-e1552265002115.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"3\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150730_095504-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150730_095504\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150730_095319-e1552265713828.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"4\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150730_095319-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150730_095319\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150623_094228-e1552265026946.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"5\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150623_094228-e1552264987412-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150623_094228\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150610_094849-e1552265744179.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"6\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150610_094849-e1552265522757-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150610_094849\" /></a></figure>			\n		<ul><li>I worked with the production team assembling pumps and testing products before shipping to the customer.</li><li>I also worked with the maintenance team fixing used pumps and learning wiring the electrical boxes that control large booster systems.</li></ul>','Experience','','inherit','closed','closed','','123-revision-v1','','','2019-03-11 01:16:03','2019-03-11 01:16:03','',123,'http://waseemorphali.com/123-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(205,1,'2019-03-13 15:13:13','2019-03-13 15:13:13','','CRC1 Diagram','','inherit','open','closed','','crc1-diagram','','','2019-03-13 15:13:13','2019-03-13 15:13:13','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(206,1,'2019-03-13 15:13:16','2019-03-13 15:13:16','','CRC0 Diagram','','inherit','open','closed','','crc0-diagram','','','2019-03-13 15:13:16','2019-03-13 15:13:16','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(207,1,'2019-03-13 15:13:20','2019-03-13 15:13:20','','CRC2 Diagram','','inherit','open','closed','','crc2-diagram','','','2019-03-13 15:13:20','2019-03-13 15:13:20','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(209,1,'2019-03-13 15:25:53','2019-03-13 15:25:53','<p>A <b>cyclic redundancy check</b> (<b>CRC</b>) is an error-detecting code commonly used in digital networks and storage devices to detect accidental changes to raw data. Blocks of data entering these systems get a short <i>check value</i> attached, based on the remainder of a polynomial division of their contents. On retrieval, the calculation is repeated and, in the event the check values do not match, corrective action can be taken against data corruption. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_redundancy_check\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia</a>)</p><p>I wrote a VHDL code to simulate user input as a number of bits and shows the output with the CRC code attached on the LEDs of the intel DE2-70</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"146\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png 676w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram-300x71.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-3</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-300x52.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-768x134.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram.png 1119w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-5</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"79\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-300x38.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-768x98.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram.png 1326w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-8</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n		<p>I simulated the circuit using the software from Intel called Quartus and showed how it works perfectly as inteded:</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"112\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc0-simulation-1024x185.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc0-simulation-1024x185.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc0-simulation-300x54.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc0-simulation-768x139.jpg 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc0-simulation.jpg 1072w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>crc0 shows the CRC-3 code to be attached</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"110\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc1-simulation-1024x182.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc1-simulation-1024x182.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc1-simulation-300x53.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc1-simulation-768x137.jpg 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc1-simulation.jpg 1100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>crc1 shows the CRC-5 code to be attached</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"112\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc2-simulation-1024x185.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc2-simulation-1024x185.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc2-simulation-300x54.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc2-simulation-768x139.jpg 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/crc2-simulation.jpg 1082w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>crc2 shows the CRC-8 code to be attached</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n		<p>I presented the circuit and code to the professor and demonstrated the how the code works on the DE2-70 board</p>		\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"349\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20181217_115414-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20181217_115414-1024x576.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20181217_115414-300x169.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20181217_115414-768x432.jpg 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20181217_115414-520x292.jpg 520w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20181217_115414-720x404.jpg 720w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />','Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA','','publish','closed','closed','','implementation-of-cyclic-redundancy-check-on-fpga','','','2019-03-14 18:31:32','2019-03-14 18:31:32','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/?page_id=209',0,'page','',0),(210,1,'2019-03-13 15:25:53','2019-03-13 15:25:53','','Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA','','inherit','closed','closed','','209-revision-v1','','','2019-03-13 15:25:53','2019-03-13 15:25:53','',209,'http://waseemorphali.com/209-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(211,1,'2019-03-13 15:26:26','2019-03-13 15:26:26','We implemented an algorithm for tree pattern matching described in the IEEE paper \"<a href=\"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/1598158\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">A Parallel Algorithm and Architecture for Object Recognition in Images</a>\".\nWe used VHDL to implement the algorithm, and we added our own designed components to control data flow through the circuit. The team consisted of 4 students, I was the leader of the group.\n\nWe used ModelSim to simulate and test the VHDL code.\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"434\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/complete-diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/complete-diagram.png 816w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/complete-diagram-300x210.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/complete-diagram-768x537.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\"><figcaption>System block diagram</figcaption></figure>\nThe system proposed in the paper uses processing elements (PEs) to process the data serially and send the result back, we designed and added memory blocks that handle data input and a controller to handle data distribution and control of the different PEs and registers. The detailed diagrams of the top and bottom parts of the system are shown below.\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"337\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/top-part-diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/top-part-diagram.png 678w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/top-part-diagram-300x163.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Top part</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"493\" height=\"456\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/bottom-part-diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/bottom-part-diagram.png 493w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/bottom-part-diagram-300x277.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 493px) 100vw, 493px\">\n\n<figcaption>Bottom part</figcaption></figure>\nThe controller is built using a state machine whose diagram is shown below.\n\n<img width=\"620\" height=\"484\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/State-Diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/State-Diagram.png 701w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/State-Diagram-300x234.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\nIn the end, we delivered a good system inspired by the paper and designed by us. Also, I gained very good experience in VHDL, and in working as part of a team on a challenging project.\n\n<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20180508_210023-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20180508_210023-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20180508_210023-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20180508_210023-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">','Implementation of Tree Pattern Matching','','publish','closed','closed','','implementation-of-tree-pattern-matching','','','2019-12-30 23:53:40','2019-12-30 23:53:40','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/?page_id=211',0,'page','',0),(212,1,'2019-03-13 15:26:26','2019-03-13 15:26:26','','Implementation of Tree Pattern Matching','','inherit','closed','closed','','211-revision-v1','','','2019-03-13 15:26:26','2019-03-13 15:26:26','',211,'http://waseemorphali.com/211-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(213,1,'2019-03-13 15:26:46','2019-03-13 15:26:46','<p>We built a system that sees the position of a toy car using a camera fixed to the ceiling and drives it automatically to the desired location.</p><p>We coded the system in MATLAB. We used image processing to identify the car\'s position and destination and we coded 3 different methods of control to guide the car to the destination.</p><p>The image processing technique we used was background subtraction. This method easily detects the car since it\'s the only object moving in the environment. A Gaussian filter was applied to reduce the noise after subtraction and then a threshold was applied and the remaining pixel locations was averaged to get the car\'s location. The process is shown below.</p>		\n				<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"1fe0c25\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"0\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car.png\" alt=\"Car\" /></a><figcaption>Car</figcaption></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/car2.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"1fe0c25\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"1\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/car2.png\" alt=\"Subtracted Background\" /></a><figcaption>Subtracted Background</figcaption></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/car3.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"1fe0c25\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"2\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/car3.png\" alt=\"Gaussian Filter\" /></a><figcaption>Gaussian Filter</figcaption></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/car4.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"1fe0c25\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"3\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/car4.png\" alt=\"Threshold Applied\" /></a><figcaption>Threshold Applied</figcaption></figure>			\n		<p>We used a cheap remote controlled toy car we bought from the local market and we modified its motor because it was too fast to be controlled accurately.</p>		\n											<a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\">\n							<img width=\"300\" height=\"225\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car-768x576.jpg 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Car.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />								</a>\n		<p>To control the car we hacked its remote controller and made our own printed circuit board (PCB) so that we can connect the PC to the remote controller.</p>		\n				<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20151109_161717-e1552616478298.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"f7c4b26\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"0\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20151109_161717-e1552616478298-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"20151109_161717\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG-20151109-WA0002-e1552616585742.jpeg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"f7c4b26\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"1\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG-20151109-WA0002-e1552616585742-768x1365.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG-20151109-WA0002\" /></a></figure>			\n		<p>The project was completed successfully and the system was able to control the car perfectly.</p><p>Shown below is the project poster.</p>		\n											<a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Project-Poster.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\">\n							<img width=\"3179\" height=\"2246\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Project-Poster.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Project-Poster.jpg 3179w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Project-Poster-300x212.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Project-Poster-768x543.jpg 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Project-Poster-1024x723.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 3179px) 100vw, 3179px\" />								</a>','Visually Servoed RC Toy Car','','publish','closed','closed','','visually-servoed-rc-toy-car','','','2019-03-15 02:35:05','2019-03-15 02:35:05','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/?page_id=213',0,'page','',0),(214,1,'2019-03-13 15:26:46','2019-03-13 15:26:46','','Visually Servoed RC Toy Car','','inherit','closed','closed','','213-revision-v1','','','2019-03-13 15:26:46','2019-03-13 15:26:46','',213,'http://waseemorphali.com/213-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2019-03-14 17:27:41','2019-03-14 17:27:41','<p>A <b>cyclic redundancy check</b> (<b>CRC</b>) is an error-detecting code commonly used in digital networks and storage devices to detect accidental changes to raw data. Blocks of data entering these systems get a short <i>check value</i> attached, based on the remainder of a polynomial division of their contents. On retrieval, the calculation is repeated and, in the event the check values do not match, corrective action can be taken against data corruption. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_redundancy_check\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia</a>)</p><p>I wrote a VHDL code to simulate user input as a number of bits and shows the output with the CRC code attached on the LEDs of the intel DE2-70</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"146\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png 676w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram-300x71.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-3</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-300x52.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-768x134.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram.png 1119w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-5</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"79\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-300x38.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-768x98.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram.png 1326w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-8</figcaption>\n										</figure>','Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA','','inherit','closed','closed','','209-revision-v1','','','2019-03-14 17:27:41','2019-03-14 17:27:41','',209,'http://waseemorphali.com/209-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(217,1,'2019-03-14 17:29:21','2019-03-14 17:29:21','<p>A <b>cyclic redundancy check</b> (<b>CRC</b>) is an error-detecting code commonly used in digital networks and storage devices to detect accidental changes to raw data. Blocks of data entering these systems get a short <i>check value</i> attached, based on the remainder of a polynomial division of their contents. On retrieval, the calculation is repeated and, in the event the check values do not match, corrective action can be taken against data corruption. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_redundancy_check\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia</a>)</p><p>I wrote a VHDL code to simulate user input as a number of bits and shows the output with the CRC code attached on the LEDs of the intel DE2-70</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"146\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png 676w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram-300x71.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-3</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-300x52.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-768x134.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram.png 1119w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-5</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"79\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-300x38.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-768x98.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram.png 1326w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-8</figcaption>\n										</figure>','Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA','','inherit','closed','closed','','209-revision-v1','','','2019-03-14 17:29:21','2019-03-14 17:29:21','',209,'http://waseemorphali.com/209-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(218,1,'2019-03-14 17:31:16','2019-03-14 17:31:16','<p>A <b>cyclic redundancy check</b> (<b>CRC</b>) is an error-detecting code commonly used in digital networks and storage devices to detect accidental changes to raw data. Blocks of data entering these systems get a short <i>check value</i> attached, based on the remainder of a polynomial division of their contents. On retrieval, the calculation is repeated and, in the event the check values do not match, corrective action can be taken against data corruption. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_redundancy_check\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia</a>)</p><p>I wrote a VHDL code to simulate user input as a number of bits and shows the output with the CRC code attached on the LEDs of the intel DE2-70</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"146\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png 676w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram-300x71.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-3</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-300x52.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-768x134.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram.png 1119w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-5</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"79\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-1024x131.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-300x38.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram-768x98.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC2-Diagram.png 1326w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-8</figcaption>\n										</figure>','Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA','','inherit','closed','closed','','209-revision-v1','','','2019-03-14 17:31:16','2019-03-14 17:31:16','',209,'http://waseemorphali.com/209-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(224,1,'2019-03-14 18:28:28','2019-03-14 18:28:28','<p>A <b>cyclic redundancy check</b> (<b>CRC</b>) is an error-detecting code commonly used in digital networks and storage devices to detect accidental changes to raw data. Blocks of data entering these systems get a short <i>check value</i> attached, based on the remainder of a polynomial division of their contents. On retrieval, the calculation is repeated and, in the event the check values do not match, corrective action can be taken against data corruption. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_redundancy_check\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia</a>)</p><p>I wrote a VHDL code to simulate user input as a number of bits and shows the output with the CRC code attached on the LEDs of the intel DE2-70</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"146\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram.png 676w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC1-Diagram-300x71.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Implementation of CRC-3</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x178.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/CRC0-Diagram-1024x17