tbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"4\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150730_095319-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150730_095319\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150623_094228-e1552265026946.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"5\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150623_094228-e1552264987412-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150623_094228\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150610_094849-e1552265744179.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"977d15a\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"6\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/20150610_094849-e1552265522757-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"20150610_094849\" /></a></figure>			\n		<ul><li>I worked with the production team assembling pumps and testing products before shipping to the customer.</li><li>I also worked with the maintenance team fixing used pumps and learning wiring the electrical boxes that control large booster systems.</li></ul><p><strong>References are available if requested</strong></p>','Experience','','inherit','closed','closed','','123-revision-v1','','','2019-12-30 23:43:36','2019-12-30 23:43:36','',123,'http://waseemorphali.com/123-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(305,1,'2019-12-30 23:46:37','2019-12-30 23:46:37','<h2><p id=\"Bsc\">Bsc. Electrical Engineering</p></h2>		\n		<p><strong>King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals</strong></p><p><strong>Jan 2011 - Dec 2015</strong></p><p><strong>GPA: 3.12 / 4</strong></p><p><strong>High Level Courses:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>PLC Programming:</strong> Learned programming Siemens PLCs using ladder programming.</li><li><strong>Process Control: </strong>PID controllers and linear systems.</li><li><strong>Power System Analysis: </strong>Used ETAP software to design and analyse power system.</li><li><strong>Telecommunication Networks</strong></li><li><strong>Analogue Communication Electronics</strong></li></ul>		\n											<a href=\"www.kfupm.edu.sa/\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"\" target=\"_blank\">\n							<img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png 150w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" />								</a>\n			<h2><p id=\"Msc\">Msc. Electrical Engneering</p></h2>		\n		<p><strong>New Jersey Institute of Technology</strong></p><p><strong>Jan 2017 - Dec 2018</strong></p><p><strong>GPA: 3.95 / 4</strong></p><p><strong>Key Courses:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>VLSI Design 1: </strong>Used Mentor Graphics tools and PSPICE to design and simulate schematics and layouts.</li><li><strong>VLSI Design 2: </strong>Learned VHDL and used it to implement a pattern matching algorithm taken from a research paper.</li><li><strong>Digital Signal Processing: </strong>Learned DSP and used VHDL to design and implement a CRC generator circuit on Intel DE2_70 board. </li><li><strong>Computer System Architecture</strong></li><li><strong>Computer Arithmetic Algorithms</strong></li></ul>		\n											<a href=\"www.njit.edu/\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"\" target=\"_blank\">\n							<img width=\"620\" height=\"256\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-300x124.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-768x316.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png 1272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />								</a>','Education','','inherit','closed','closed','','117-revision-v1','','','2019-12-30 23:46:37','2019-12-30 23:46:37','',117,'http://waseemorphali.com/117-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(306,1,'2019-12-30 23:48:07','2019-12-30 23:48:07','<h2><p id=\"Msc\">Msc. Electrical Engneering</p></h2>		\n		<p><strong>New Jersey Institute of Technology</strong></p><p><strong>Jan 2017 - Dec 2018</strong></p><p><strong>GPA: 3.95 / 4</strong></p><p><strong>Key Courses:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>VLSI Design 1: </strong>Used Mentor Graphics tools and PSPICE to design and simulate schematics and layouts.</li><li><strong>VLSI Design 2: </strong>Learned VHDL and used it to implement a pattern matching algorithm taken from a research paper.</li><li><strong>Digital Signal Processing: </strong>Learned DSP and used VHDL to design and implement a CRC generator circuit on Intel DE2_70 board. </li><li><strong>Computer System Architecture</strong></li><li><strong>Computer Arithmetic Algorithms</strong></li></ul>		\n											<a href=\"www.njit.edu/\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"\" target=\"_blank\">\n							<img width=\"620\" height=\"256\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-300x124.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-768x316.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png 1272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />								</a>\n			<h2><p id=\"Bsc\">Bsc. Electrical Engineering</p></h2>		\n		<p><strong>King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals</strong></p><p><strong>Jan 2011 - Dec 2015</strong></p><p><strong>GPA: 3.12 / 4</strong></p><p><strong>High Level Courses:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>PLC Programming:</strong> Learned programming Siemens PLCs using ladder programming.</li><li><strong>Process Control: </strong>PID controllers and linear systems.</li><li><strong>Power System Analysis: </strong>Used ETAP software to design and analyse power system.</li><li><strong>Telecommunication Networks</strong></li><li><strong>Analogue Communication Electronics</strong></li></ul>		\n											<a href=\"www.kfupm.edu.sa/\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"\" target=\"_blank\">\n							<img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png 150w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" />								</a>','Education','','inherit','closed','closed','','117-revision-v1','','','2019-12-30 23:48:07','2019-12-30 23:48:07','',117,'http://waseemorphali.com/117-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2019-12-30 23:52:31','2019-12-30 23:52:31','I designed a system that is used to keep track of chores in the house and the which user is supposed to do them.\n\nI used a PIC16f88 micro controller for this project. I programmed it in C using MPLAB X IDE.\n\nFor interfacing, I used a 16x2 LCD for output and 4 debounced push buttons for input. I designed a custom PCB for the project and I\'m planning on making a 3-D printed enclosure for it.\n\nthe figures below shows the schematic and layout of the system.\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"442\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-300x214.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-768x547.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic.png 1165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\"><figcaption>Schematic</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"502\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png 897w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-300x243.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-768x622.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Layout</figcaption></figure>\nI used the tools provided by easyeda.com to create the schematic and layout of the circuit.\n\nThe circuit has 4 push buttons, but only two of them are used, the rest are left if I want to expand the functionality later on. They are wired and ready to be used, they only need to be programmed through the header pins on the left of the LCD.\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption></figure>','Chores Tracker using PIC16f88 MCU','','publish','closed','closed','','chores-tracker-using-pic16f88-mcu','','','2019-12-31 00:50:50','2019-12-31 00:50:50','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/?page_id=307',0,'page','',0),(308,1,'2019-12-30 23:50:10','2019-12-30 23:50:10','','Elementor #307','','inherit','closed','closed','','307-revision-v1','','','2019-12-30 23:50:10','2019-12-30 23:50:10','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2019-12-30 23:52:55','2019-12-30 23:52:55','','Home Improvement using PIC16f88 MCU','','inherit','closed','closed','','307-revision-v1','','','2019-12-30 23:52:55','2019-12-30 23:52:55','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2019-12-31 00:29:46','2019-12-31 00:29:46','','Schematic','Schematic','inherit','open','closed','','schematic','','','2019-12-31 00:30:04','2019-12-31 00:30:04','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(313,1,'2019-12-31 00:31:29','2019-12-31 00:31:29','','Layout','Layout','inherit','open','closed','','layout','','','2019-12-31 00:31:39','2019-12-31 00:31:39','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(314,1,'2019-12-31 00:35:48','2019-12-31 00:35:48','','Finished Product','Finished Product','inherit','open','closed','','img_20191230_190339','','','2019-12-31 00:36:17','2019-12-31 00:36:17','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(315,1,'2019-12-31 00:37:21','2019-12-31 00:37:21','','Finished Product','Finished Product','inherit','open','closed','','img_20191230_190350','','','2019-12-31 00:37:39','2019-12-31 00:37:39','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(316,1,'2019-12-31 00:38:41','2019-12-31 00:38:41','<p>I designed a system that is used to keep track of chores in the house and the which user is supposed to do them.</p><p>I used a PIC16f88 micro controller for this project. I programmed it in C using MPLAB X IDE.</p><p>For interfacing, I used a 16x2 LCD for output and 4 debounced push buttons for input. I designed a custom PCB for the project and I\'m planning on making a 3-D printed enclosure for it.</p><p>the figures below shows the schematic and layout of the system.</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"442\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-300x214.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-768x547.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic.png 1165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Schematic</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"502\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png 897w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-300x243.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-768x622.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Layout</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n		<p>I used the tools provided by easyeda.com to create the schematic and layout of the circuit.</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption>\n										</figure>','Home Improvement using PIC16f88 MCU','','inherit','closed','closed','','307-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:38:41','2019-12-31 00:38:41','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(335,1,'2019-12-31 01:29:43','2019-12-31 01:29:43','<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/\">Education</a></h2>\n<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Bsc\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"225\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png 225w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\"></a></figure>\n<h3><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Bsc\">Bsc. Electrical Engineering</a></h3>\nKing Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals\n<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Msc\"><img width=\"1272\" height=\"524\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png 1272w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-300x124.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-768x316.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1272px) 100vw, 1272px\"></a></figure>\n<h3><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Msc\">Msc. Electrical Engineering</a></h3>\nNew Jersey Institute of Technology\n<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/\">Experience</a></h2>\n<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/\">Senior Coach</a></h2>\n<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/#2\">Student Associate</a></h2>\n<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/#3\">Intern</a></h2>\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Jan 2019 - Present\n\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;July 2018 - Dec 2018\n\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;June 2015 - Aug 2015\n<h2>\n<p id=\"Projects\">Projects</p>\n</h2>\n<a href=\"\">Chores Tracker using PIC16f88 MCU</a>\n\nNov 2019\n\n<a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/Chores-Tracker-using-pic16f88-mcu/\">Click here</a>\n\nI created&nbsp; a system to keep track of chores in the house using a PIC16f88 micro controller. I programmed the micro controller in C.\n\n<a href=\"\">Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA</a>\n\nDec 2018\n\n<a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/implementation-of-cyclic-redundancy-check-on-fpga/\">Click here</a>\n\nI implemented three Cyclic Redundancy Check algorithms (CRC-8 , CRC-5 , CRC-3) on Intle’s FPGA board DE2-70 using VHDL.\n\n<a href=\"\">Implementation of Tree Pattern Matching</a>\n\nMay 2018\n\n<a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/implementation-of-tree-pattern-matching/\">Click Here</a>\n\nWe implemented an algorithm for tree pattern matching described in the IEEE paper “A Parallel Algorithm and Architecture for Object Recognition in Images”.\n\nWe used VHDL to implement the algorithm, and we added our own designed components to control data flow through the circuit.\n\n<a href=\"\">Design of a Wearable Augmented Reality System</a>\n\nMay 2017\n\nDesigned a simple augmented reality system using available components in the market.\n\n<a href=\"\">Visually Servoed RC Toy Car</a>\n\nDec 2015\n\n<a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/visually-servoed-rc-toy-car/\">Click Here</a>\n\nIt was my capstone project for my undergraduate degree.&nbsp;We built a system that senses the position of a toy car and drives it automatically to the desired location through a PC.\n\n<a href=\"\">Power System Design and Analysis</a>\n\nMay 2015\n\nLearned how to use ETAP software and designed a simple power network and analyzed it.\n<h2>\n<p id=\"Skills\">Skills</p>\n</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Microsoft Office Suite</li>\n 	<li>C</li>\n 	<li>Python</li>\n 	<li>Matlab</li>\n 	<li>Assembly</li>\n 	<li>VHDL</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Mentor Graphics</li>\n 	<li>HSPICE</li>\n 	<li>PLC Programming</li>\n 	<li>Arduino</li>\n 	<li>Fusion 360</li>\n 	<li>Languages: English, Arabic, Spanish (elementary)</li>\n</ul>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 01:29:43','2019-12-31 01:29:43','',11,'http://waseemorphali.com/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2019-12-31 00:50:09','2019-12-31 00:50:09','<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/\">Education</a></h2>		\n			<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Bsc\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"225\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png 225w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\" /></a></figure><h3><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Bsc\">Bsc. Electrical Engineering</a></h3><p>King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals</p>		\n			<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Msc\"><img width=\"1272\" height=\"524\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png 1272w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-300x124.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-768x316.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1272px) 100vw, 1272px\" /></a></figure><h3><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Msc\">Msc. Electrical Engineering</a></h3><p>New Jersey Institute of Technology</p>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/\">Experience</a></h2>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/\">Senior Coach</a></h2>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/#2\">Student Associate</a></h2>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/#3\">Intern</a></h2>		\n		<p>                   Jan 2019 - Present</p><p>                   July 2018 - Dec 2018</p><p>                   June 2015 - Aug 2015</p>		\n			<h2><p id=\"Projects\">Projects</p></h2>		\n												<a href=\"\">Chores Tracker using PIC16f88 MCU</a>\n					<p>Nov 2019</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/home-improvement-using-pic16f88-mcu/\">Click here</a></p><p>I created  a system to keep track of chores in the house using a PIC16f88 micro controller. I programmed the micro controller in C.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA</a>\n					<p>Dec 2018</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/implementation-of-cyclic-redundancy-check-on-fpga/\">Click here</a></p><p>I implemented three Cyclic Redundancy Check algorithms (CRC-8 , CRC-5 , CRC-3) on Intle&#8217;s FPGA board DE2-70 using VHDL.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Implementation of Tree Pattern Matching</a>\n					<p>May 2018</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/implementation-of-tree-pattern-matching/\">Click Here</a></p><p>We implemented an algorithm for tree pattern matching described in the IEEE paper &#8220;A Parallel Algorithm and Architecture for Object Recognition in Images&#8221;.</p><p>We used VHDL to implement the algorithm, and we added our own designed components to control data flow through the circuit.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Design of a Wearable Augmented Reality System</a>\n					<p>May 2017</p><p>Designed a simple augmented reality system using available components in the market.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Visually Servoed RC Toy Car</a>\n					<p>Dec 2015</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/visually-servoed-rc-toy-car/\">Click Here</a></p><p>It was my capstone project for my undergraduate degree. We built a system that senses the position of a toy car and drives it automatically to the desired location through a PC.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Power System Design and Analysis</a>\n					<p>May 2015</p><p>Learned how to use ETAP software and designed a simple power network and analyzed it.</p>\n			<h2><p id=\"Skills\">Skills</p></h2>		\n		<ul><li>Microsoft Office Suite</li><li>C</li><li>Python</li><li>Matlab</li><li>Assembly</li><li>VHDL</li></ul><ul><li>Mentor Graphics</li><li>HSPICE</li><li>PLC Programming</li><li>Arduino</li><li>Fusion 360</li><li>Languages: English, Arabic, Spanish (elementary)</li></ul>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:50:09','2019-12-31 00:50:09','',11,'http://waseemorphali.com/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2019-12-31 00:48:18','2019-12-31 00:48:18','<p>I designed a system that is used to keep track of chores in the house and the which user is supposed to do them.</p><p>I used a PIC16f88 micro controller for this project. I programmed it in C using MPLAB X IDE.</p><p>For interfacing, I used a 16x2 LCD for output and 4 debounced push buttons for input. I designed a custom PCB for the project and I\'m planning on making a 3-D printed enclosure for it.</p><p>the figures below shows the schematic and layout of the system.</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"442\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-300x214.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-768x547.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic.png 1165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Schematic</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"502\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png 897w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-300x243.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-768x622.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Layout</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n		<p>I used the tools provided by easyeda.com to create the schematic and layout of the circuit.</p><p>The circuit has 4 push buttons, but only 2 of the are used, the rest are left if I want to expand the functionality later on. They are wired and ready to be used, they only need to be programmed through the header pins on the left of the LCD.</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption>\n										</figure>','Home Improvement using PIC16f88 MCU','','inherit','closed','closed','','307-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:48:18','2019-12-31 00:48:18','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2019-12-31 00:50:50','2019-12-31 00:50:50','I designed a system that is used to keep track of chores in the house and the which user is supposed to do them.\n\nI used a PIC16f88 micro controller for this project. I programmed it in C using MPLAB X IDE.\n\nFor interfacing, I used a 16x2 LCD for output and 4 debounced push buttons for input. I designed a custom PCB for the project and I\'m planning on making a 3-D printed enclosure for it.\n\nthe figures below shows the schematic and layout of the system.\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"442\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-300x214.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-768x547.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic.png 1165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\"><figcaption>Schematic</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"502\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png 897w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-300x243.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-768x622.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Layout</figcaption></figure>\nI used the tools provided by easyeda.com to create the schematic and layout of the circuit.\n\nThe circuit has 4 push buttons, but only two of them are used, the rest are left if I want to expand the functionality later on. They are wired and ready to be used, they only need to be programmed through the header pins on the left of the LCD.\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\">\n\n<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption></figure>','Chores Tracker using PIC16f88 MCU','','inherit','closed','closed','','307-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:50:50','2019-12-31 00:50:50','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2019-12-31 00:48:55','2019-12-31 00:48:55','<p>I designed a system that is used to keep track of chores in the house and the which user is supposed to do them.</p><p>I used a PIC16f88 micro controller for this project. I programmed it in C using MPLAB X IDE.</p><p>For interfacing, I used a 16x2 LCD for output and 4 debounced push buttons for input. I designed a custom PCB for the project and I\'m planning on making a 3-D printed enclosure for it.</p><p>the figures below shows the schematic and layout of the system.</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"442\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-1024x730.png 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-300x214.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic-768x547.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Schematic.png 1165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Schematic</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"502\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout.png 897w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-300x243.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Layout-768x622.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Layout</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n		<p>I used the tools provided by easyeda.com to create the schematic and layout of the circuit.</p><p>The circuit has 4 push buttons, but only two of them are used, the rest are left if I want to expand the functionality later on. They are wired and ready to be used, they only need to be programmed through the header pins on the left of the LCD.</p>		\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190339-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption>\n										</figure>\n							<figure>\n										<img width=\"620\" height=\"465\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-300x225.jpg 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_190350-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" />											<figcaption>Finished Product</figcaption>\n										</figure>','Home Improvement using PIC16f88 MCU','','inherit','closed','closed','','307-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:48:55','2019-12-31 00:48:55','',307,'http://waseemorphali.com/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(322,1,'2019-12-31 00:51:14','2019-12-31 00:51:14','<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/\">Education</a></h2>		\n			<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Bsc\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"225\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download.png 225w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/download-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\" /></a></figure><h3><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Bsc\">Bsc. Electrical Engineering</a></h3><p>King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals</p>		\n			<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Msc\"><img width=\"1272\" height=\"524\" src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology.png 1272w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-300x124.png 300w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-768x316.png 768w, http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Logo_of_New_Jersey_Institute_of_Technology-1024x422.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1272px) 100vw, 1272px\" /></a></figure><h3><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/education/#Msc\">Msc. Electrical Engineering</a></h3><p>New Jersey Institute of Technology</p>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/\">Experience</a></h2>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/\">Senior Coach</a></h2>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/#2\">Student Associate</a></h2>		\n			<h2><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/experience/#3\">Intern</a></h2>		\n		<p>                   Jan 2019 - Present</p><p>                   July 2018 - Dec 2018</p><p>                   June 2015 - Aug 2015</p>		\n			<h2><p id=\"Projects\">Projects</p></h2>		\n												<a href=\"\">Chores Tracker using PIC16f88 MCU</a>\n					<p>Nov 2019</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/Chores-Tracker-using-pic16f88-mcu/\">Click here</a></p><p>I created  a system to keep track of chores in the house using a PIC16f88 micro controller. I programmed the micro controller in C.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Implementation of Cyclic Redundancy Check on FPGA</a>\n					<p>Dec 2018</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/implementation-of-cyclic-redundancy-check-on-fpga/\">Click here</a></p><p>I implemented three Cyclic Redundancy Check algorithms (CRC-8 , CRC-5 , CRC-3) on Intle&#8217;s FPGA board DE2-70 using VHDL.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Implementation of Tree Pattern Matching</a>\n					<p>May 2018</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/implementation-of-tree-pattern-matching/\">Click Here</a></p><p>We implemented an algorithm for tree pattern matching described in the IEEE paper &#8220;A Parallel Algorithm and Architecture for Object Recognition in Images&#8221;.</p><p>We used VHDL to implement the algorithm, and we added our own designed components to control data flow through the circuit.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Design of a Wearable Augmented Reality System</a>\n					<p>May 2017</p><p>Designed a simple augmented reality system using available components in the market.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Visually Servoed RC Toy Car</a>\n					<p>Dec 2015</p><p><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/visually-servoed-rc-toy-car/\">Click Here</a></p><p>It was my capstone project for my undergraduate degree. We built a system that senses the position of a toy car and drives it automatically to the desired location through a PC.</p>\n												<a href=\"\">Power System Design and Analysis</a>\n					<p>May 2015</p><p>Learned how to use ETAP software and designed a simple power network and analyzed it.</p>\n			<h2><p id=\"Skills\">Skills</p></h2>		\n		<ul><li>Microsoft Office Suite</li><li>C</li><li>Python</li><li>Matlab</li><li>Assembly</li><li>VHDL</li></ul><ul><li>Mentor Graphics</li><li>HSPICE</li><li>PLC Programming</li><li>Arduino</li><li>Fusion 360</li><li>Languages: English, Arabic, Spanish (elementary)</li></ul>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:51:14','2019-12-31 00:51:14','',11,'http://waseemorphali.com/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(323,1,'2019-12-31 00:58:46','2019-12-31 00:58:46','<p>I wanted to connect the AC thermostat in the house we are living in right now to the internet so we can control it through our phones instead of having to do it manually. So I designed and built a system to do that.</p><p>I designed a mechanical module with a servo motor that can be taped on the thermostat to control it, and I connected the servo motor to the ESP01 micro controller. ESP01 is an IOT micro controller that can be programmed using different methods, I programmed it using the Arduion IDE.</p><p>I used an APP called Blynk to to connect to the phone because it\'s free and it provides a very good GUI.</p><p>Since we are not the owners of the house, I didn\'t want to change anything in the wiring of the thermostat or do any permanent changes.</p>		\n				<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120557-e1577755298398.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"64a2157\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"0\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120557-e1577755298398-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"Finished System\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120622-e1577755468609.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"64a2157\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"1\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120622-e1577755468609-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20191230_120622\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120713-e1577755480682.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"64a2157\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"2\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120713-e1577755480682-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20191230_120713\" /></a></figure>			\n		<p>I got the pinion gear and pusher design from a listing on <a href=\"https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3170748\">thingiverse</a> and I modified them to fit what I need. I also designed the enclosure for the electronics.</p>		\n				<figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Capture2.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"b50fd65\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"0\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Capture2-320x320.png\" alt=\"Electronics housing\" /></a></figure><figure><a href=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Capture.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"b50fd65\" data-elementor-lightbox-index=\"1\"><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Capture-320x320.png\" alt=\"Motor bracket and pusher\" /></a></figure>','Wi-Fi Enabled AC Thermostat','','publish','closed','closed','','wi-fi-enabled-ac-thermostat','','','2019-12-31 01:55:31','2019-12-31 01:55:31','',0,'http://waseemorphali.com/?page_id=323',0,'page','',0),(324,1,'2019-12-31 00:58:46','2019-12-31 00:58:46','','WI-FI Enabled AC Thermostat','','inherit','closed','closed','','323-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 00:58:46','2019-12-31 00:58:46','',323,'http://waseemorphali.com/323-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(325,1,'2019-12-31 01:13:07','2019-12-31 01:13:07','<p>I wanted to connect the AC thermostat in the house we are living in right now to the internet so we can control it through our phones instead of having to do it manually. So I designed and built a system to do that.</p><p>I designed a mechanical module with a servo motor that can be taped on the thermostat to control it, and I connected the servo motor to the ESP01 micro controller. ESP01 is an IOT micro controller that can be programmed using different methods, I programmed it using the Arduion IDE.</p><p>I used an APP called Blynk to to connect to the phone because it\'s free and it provides a very good GUI.</p><p>Since we are not the owners of the house, I didn\'t want to change anything in the wiring of the thermostat or do any permanent changes.</p>','WI-FI Enabled AC Thermostat','','inherit','closed','closed','','323-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 01:13:07','2019-12-31 01:13:07','',323,'http://waseemorphali.com/323-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(333,1,'2019-12-31 01:26:35','2019-12-31 01:26:35','<p>I wanted to connect the AC thermostat in the house we are living in right now to the internet so we can control it through our phones instead of having to do it manually. So I designed and built a system to do that.</p><p>I designed a mechanical module with a servo motor that can be taped on the thermostat to control it, and I connected the servo motor to the ESP01 micro controller. ESP01 is an IOT micro controller that can be programmed using different methods, I programmed it using the Arduion IDE.</p><p>I used an APP called Blynk to to connect to the phone because it\'s free and it provides a very good GUI.</p><p>Since we are not the owners of the house, I didn\'t want to change anything in the wiring of the thermostat or do any permanent changes.</p>		\n				<figure><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120557-e1577755298398-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"Finished System\" /></figure><figure><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120622-e1577755468609-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20191230_120622\" /></figure><figure><img src=\"http://waseemorphali.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_20191230_120713-e1577755480682-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20191230_120713\" /></figure>','WI-FI Enabled AC Thermostat','','inherit','closed','closed','','323-revision-v1','','','2019-12-31 01:26:35','2019-12-31 01:26:35','',323,'http://waseemorphali.com/